
mydu
	mydu is a modified implementation of the du command, returning the sizes of directories indicated by the command line, or the current directory if no path is indicated, as well as the sizes of subdirectories


Installation
	After download, navigate to the directory containing the source/header files. From the command line, enter "make -f makeMYDU"



Usage
	From the directory containing the mydu executable:
./mydu    // prints sizes of current directory and its subdirectory
./mydu .. pathName    // prints sizes of parent directory and its subdirectories, then prints sizes of directory/file indicated by pathName, and of any subdirectories 
./mydu -h    // prints description of mydu, including all possible options


Hierarchy of Command Line Options
	If conflicting command line options are selected, they will be overridden as follows:
-H > -B M > -m > -b
-s > -d N > -a


Version Control
	Git was used for version control. The full commit history can be viewed at http://github.com/adwzq4/OS-Project-1/commits/master


